# Capability vocabulary v0 — grounded in M-trip-journal hinge-log evidence

**IF:** a hinge-log entry records the operator crossing a structural cleavage in mission work.
**HOWEVER:** the capability is only visible at the hinge if it was articulated — silent competence is invisible (M-learning-loop checkpoint-1, articulation-floor noise).
**THEN:** tag the hinge with the capability dimension(s) it evidences, at the confidence the evidence supports.
**BECAUSE:** the mining loop's output vocabulary must be constrained to what a downstream navigable hypergraph consumes — unconstrained discourse paraphrase is the over-firing failure mode (the meme miner over-fired "new pattern" at 95%).
**NEXT-STEPS:** default to "no-capability-shift" (the common case); anchor rare labels (new-capability, capability-stalled) with frequency expectations so the tagger does not over-fire them.
